      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear-elastic isotropic titanium alloy constitutive model justified by strain gauge data confirming sub-yield loading; frictional contact formulation validated against slip measurements.",
      "rationale": "Strain gauge measurements on representative constructs confirm that titanium alloy components remain within the linear-elastic regime throughout the F1717 test protocol. A bilinear isotropic hardening model was evaluated and produced equivalent QoI predictions (<0.5% difference), confirming the linear-elastic form is appropriate. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) was selected based on tribological literature for Ti-6Al-4V on Ti-6Al-4V."
